-- South Korean Stocks: Hyundai Heavy, Hyundai Motor, NCsoft, OCI
-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 2012-07-17T07:46:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/south-korean-stocks-hyundai-heavy-hyundai-motor-ncsoft-oci.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  South Korea  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Seoul. The Kospi
index added 0.2 percent to 1,821.96, rising for a third day.  Hyundai Motor Co. (005380 KS), South Korea’s biggest
carmaker, slipped 2.4 percent to 223,000 won.  Hyundai Heavy
Industries Co. (009540)  (009540 KS) sold 3.2 million shares of Hyundai
Motor at 220,000 won apiece, or 3.7 percent lower than
yesterday’s price, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.
Hyundai Heavy shares added 0.9 percent to 238,500 won.  NCsoft Corp. (036570)  (036570 KS), an online-game maker, added 6.2
percent to 222,000 won, after tumbling 6.7 percent yesterday.
The recent drop in the share-price is “excessive,” Lee Chang Young, an analyst at Tong Yang Securities Inc., said in a
report.  OCI Co. (010060)  (010060 KS), South Korea’s biggest polysilicon
maker, retreated 3.5 percent to 204,500 won. China has started a
probe into possible polysilicon dumping by South Korea, Edaily
reported, citing unidentified industry officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
